# Git Commands

This document contains commonly used Git commands with their purpose and examples.

---

# Check Git Version

Displays the installed Git version.

```bash
git --version
```

Example:

```bash
git version 2.50.1.windows.1
```

---

# Configure Username

Sets your Git username.

```bash
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
```

---

# Configure Email

Sets your Git email.

```bash
git config --global user.email "your@email.com"
```

---

# View Git Configuration

Displays all configured Git settings.

```bash
git config --list
```

---

# Initialize a Repository

Creates a new Git repository.

```bash
git init
```

---

# Clone a Repository

Downloads an existing repository from GitHub.

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
```

Example:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/username/project.git
```

---

# Check Status

Shows the current state of your repository.

```bash
git status
```

---

# Stage a File

Adds a specific file to the staging area.

```bash
git add filename
```

Example:

```bash
git add README.md
```

---

# Stage All Files

Adds all modified files.

```bash
git add .
```

---

# Commit Changes

Saves staged changes.

```bash
git commit -m "Your commit message"
```

Example:

```bash
git commit -m "Added README file"
```

---

# View Commit History

Displays all commits.

```bash
git log
```

---

# View Short Commit History

Displays commits in one line.

```bash
git log --oneline
```

---

# Create a Branch

```bash
git branch branch-name
```

Example:

```bash
git branch feature
```

---

# List All Branches

```bash
git branch
```

---

# Switch Branch

```bash
git checkout branch-name
```

or

```bash
git switch branch-name
```

---

# Create and Switch to a Branch

```bash
git checkout -b branch-name
```

or

```bash
git switch -c branch-name
```

---

# Merge a Branch

```bash
git merge branch-name
```

---

# Delete a Branch

```bash
git branch -d branch-name
```

---

# Add Remote Repository

```bash
git remote add origin <repository-url>
```

---

# View Remote Repositories

```bash
git remote -v
```

---

# Push Changes

```bash
git push origin main
```

---

# Push First Time

```bash
git push -u origin main
```

---

# Pull Latest Changes

```bash
git pull origin main
```

---

# Fetch Changes

Downloads changes without merging.

```bash
git fetch
```

---

# Remove a File

```bash
git rm filename
```

---

# Rename a File

```bash
git mv oldname newname
```

---

# Undo Last Commit (Keep Changes)

```bash
git reset --soft HEAD~1
```

---

# Undo Last Commit (Remove Changes)

```bash
git reset --hard HEAD~1
```

---

# Restore a File

```bash
git restore filename
```

---

# Stash Changes

Temporarily saves uncommitted changes.

```bash
git stash
```

---

# Apply Stashed Changes

```bash
git stash apply
```

---

# List Stashes

```bash
git stash list
```

---

# Delete a Stash

```bash
git stash drop
```

---

# Current Branch

```bash
git branch --show-current
```

---

# Show Differences

```bash
git diff
```

---

# Display Help

```bash
git help
```

or

```bash
git <command> --help
```

Example:

```bash
git commit --help
```

---

# Summary

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|----------|
| `git init` | Initialize a repository |
| `git clone` | Clone a repository |
| `git status` | Check repository status |
| `git add` | Stage files |
| `git commit` | Save changes |
| `git log` | View commit history |
| `git branch` | Manage branches |
| `git checkout` | Switch branches |
| `git merge` | Merge branches |
| `git remote` | Manage remotes |
| `git push` | Upload changes |
| `git pull` | Download and merge changes |
| `git fetch` | Download changes only |
| `git reset` | Undo commits |
| `git restore` | Restore files |
| `git stash` | Save temporary changes |
| `git diff` | View file differences |
